            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-3-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-3-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Slice your <strong>flat white mushrooms </strong>finely</p><p>Chop your <strong>chestnut mushrooms </strong>in half</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-4-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-4-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-4-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-4-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-4-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the pepper has cooled slightly, transfer it to a<strong> food processor</strong> with your<strong> chilli flakes</strong> (can't handle the heat? Go easy!)</p><p>Add the juice of<strong> half</strong> your <strong>lime[s]</strong> with your <strong>pumpkin seeds</strong> and a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and <strong>pepper</strong></p><p>Blitz until you have a chunky sauce – this is your<strong> red pepper salsa</strong></p>",
      "order": 5,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-5-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-5-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-5-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-5-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-5-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the onions have softened, add the <strong>sliced flat white mushrooms</strong> and<strong> halved chestnut mushrooms</strong> to the pan with your <strong>chipotle paste </strong>(not a fan of spice? Just add a little!),<strong> soy sauce</strong> and <strong>smoked paprika</strong></p><p>Cook for 4-5 min further or until the mushrooms have started to soften – these are your <strong>chipotle mushrooms</strong></p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-6-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-6-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-6-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-6-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-6-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Chop your<strong> coriander</strong> roughly, including the stalks</p><p>Once the rice is cooked, add the <strong>chopped coriander</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong> and the<strong> </strong>juice<strong> </strong>of the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>lime</strong> and give everything a good mix up – this is your<strong> zingy coriander rice</strong></p><p>Add your<strong> tortillas</strong> to a plate and <strong>microwave </strong>for 30 secs or until warmed through</p>",
      "order": 7,
      "media": {
        "images": [
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-7-x200.jpg",
            "width": 200
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-7-x400.jpg",
            "width": 400
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-7-x700.jpg",
            "width": 700
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-7-x1000.jpg",
            "width": 1000
          },
          {
            "image": "https://production-media.gousto.co.uk/cms/recipe-step-image/RC2363Step-7-x1500.jpg",
            "width": 1500
          }
        ]
      }
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Assemble the <strong>warmed</strong> <strong>tortillas</strong> with some <strong>zingy coriander rice</strong> and the <strong>chipotle mushrooms</strong></p><p>Top with the <strong>pepper salsa</strong> and<strong> soured cream</strong></p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
      "order": 8,
